<DOC><DOCNO> AP881003-0011 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-10-03-88 0027EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r i PM-Papandreou     10-03 0159</FIRST><SECOND>PM-Papandreou,0164</SECOND><HEAD>Greek Premier Recovering From Heart Operation</HEAD><DATELINE>HAREFIELD, England (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Two days after his heart surgery,Prime Minister Andreas Papandreou of Greece was able to get out ofbed and walk, a Harefield Hospital spokesman said.   The 69-year-old leader underwent six hours of surgery on Fridayto replace a diseased aortic valve.   ``He is fine. There are no problems or complications,'' said ahospital spokesman on Sunday. He said Papandreou was able to walkaround the intensive care unit of the hospital.   Papandreou was restricted over the weekend to visits from histhree sons, his daughter and his companion, Dimitra Liani. Hiswife, whom he said he is divorcing, did not come to Britain.   If Papandreou continues to make good progress, he could be outof the hospital in 10 days.   The Greek leader flew to Britain last month suffering fromnarrowing of the main heart artery and underwent treatment to readyhim for the operation.</TEXT></DOC>